description:
When writing awaiting state, clear the Manual field

When setting Awaiting on a tick:
- Clear Manual field to avoid confusion
- Only use Awaiting field going forward

Implementation:
Add method to tick.go:

func (t *Tick) SetAwaiting(value string) {
    if value == "" {
        t.Awaiting = nil
    } else {
        t.Awaiting = &value
    }
    t.Manual = false  // Clear old field
}

All code setting awaiting should use this method or explicitly clear Manual.

This ensures:
- New ticks use Awaiting, not Manual
- Updated ticks migrate from Manual to Awaiting
- No tick has both Manual=true and Awaiting set
